headline: Allstate issues new guidance to protect shoppers as identity scams surge ahead of the holidays
summary: Identity theft is ramping up earlier than expected. New data from Allstate Identity Protection1 shows a sharp rise in fraudulent account activity in October, surpassing November and December. The surge coincides with early holiday shopping and digital promotions, exposing consumers to increased financial risk.
